        <h2>About This Page</h2>
        <p>This is a simple homepage designed to give you a starting point for learning C++. You'll find resources, tutorials, and more!</p>

        <section>
            <h2>History of C++</h2>
            <p>C++ was created by Bjarne Stroustrup at Bell Labs in 1979 as an enhancement to the C language. Stroustrup wanted to combine the efficiency of C with object-oriented features like classes and inheritance.</p>

            <p>In 1983, the language was renamed C++ and introduced key features like virtual functions and function overloading. In 1998, it was officially standardized as **C++98**, and further revisions, such as **C++11**, brought new features like the **auto keyword**, **lambda expressions**, and **concurrency** support.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>Key Milestones:</h2>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>1979</strong>: Creation of C++ (C with Classes).</li>
                <li><strong>1983</strong>: Renamed C++ and added major features.</li>
                <li><strong>1998</strong>: C++ standardized as **C++98**.</li>
                <li><strong>2011</strong>: Release of **C++11**, introducing modern features like **auto** and **lambda expressions**.</li>
                <li><strong>2020</strong>: Release of **C++20** with more powerful tools like **concepts** and **coroutines**.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>
